sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1129014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The constitutive promoter comes from part BBa_J23118, found in Plate 1 of the 2012 Distribution Kit. The gene comes from TU Munich 2012 part BBa_K801071 in the 2013 Distribution Kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CaMXMT1 is the gene coding for the second enzyme of the caffeine biosynthesis pathway, known as 7-methylxanthosine N-methyltransferase or theobromine synthase, when starting with xanthosine as substrate. TU Munich's 2012 team isolated this gene and added a strep tag at the end, in addition to transferring it all into yeast. We modified it further by removing the yeast consensus sequence and placing the gene and strep tag behind a constitutive promoter and bacterial consensus sequence. This system was transformed into a prokaryote, specifically E. coli strain K12. We have yet to test for expression, and we may find that codon optimization is needed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Codon optimization has not yet been performed, but we suspect it may be needed for successful expression in a prokaryotic system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: UBC iGEM 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K801071
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthesized by IDT, Yeast codon optimized
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 7-methylxanthine N-methyltransferase CaMXMT1 from ''Coffea arabica'' followed by a strep-tag for purification and/or detection via western blot.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Roman Prechtl

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
